file_content.text: Well, it's about time! Do you have any idea how long I've been sitting in that cell, Republic dog? Now get me out of here.
Just hold tight, there. I'll have you out in no time.
That's what I'm here for.
Damn Republic misses the meet and hangs me out to dry, and then this lout has the nerve to tell me to "hold tight."
You should be grateful.
If the Republic wants gratitude, they should show up for the meeting on time.
I'm beginning to think it might not be such a bad idea to kill you.
You're scum.
Is this some lame attempt at a double-cross? Let's make one thing clear: You are here to free me.
You do not think on your own. You do not act on your own. You do what I tell you, or the Republic will have your head.
So now, do you still want to kill me?
You're nothing but a pirate turned snitch. You're in way more trouble than I am.
You think you impress me?
Just kidding.
I thought so.
So are we going to get out of here now or what?
Get out of here.
Go!
I'm killing you right here and now.
No, you're dead.
I wanna kill you more than I have ever wanted to kill anyone.
Yes.
Listen to me, dog. Kill me, and the Republic will never forget it.
So what'll it be, dog? Are you really going to kill me, and put your own head on the Republic's chopping block?
Get going--the Republic will see to it you're kept safe.
No, I was out of line.
That's right. You know your place.
Move!
Just doing my job.
I'm already starting to regret letting you go.
Don't make me change my mind.
Well, I don't like you much either, so goodbye.
I assume the Republic's got agents outside to extend even more of this fine "protection." I'll be sure to tell them you did a perfectly adequate job, for a nitwit.
You die right here and right now.
Yes.
Argh!
